Description: Rim fragment of a stone vessel made of calcite, rounded-square rim section, well polished at the outside and inside. The diameter of the rim is between 8 and 10cm suggesting a beaker or vase-like shape.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), Temple East Sanctuary
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
